    "title": "Immediate Requirement Logistics Manager at IRCTC Logistics",
    "description": "Join the IRCTC Logistics family as a Logistics Manager in Gurgaon. We believe in empowering our employees with the tools, training, and environment they need to succeed.\n\nAbout IRCTC Logistics:\nIRCTC Logistics is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Prepare MIS reports on delivery performance and SLA adherence\n• Ensure compliance with transportation regulations and safety standards\n• Ensure proper handling, packaging, and labeling of goods\n• Conduct periodic vendor audits and evaluate logistics partners\n• Oversee end-to-end logistics operations for timely delivery\n• Handle customs clearance for import and export shipments\n• Manage a fleet of vehicles and coordinate with drivers\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Ed / M.Ed from a recognized institution\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Supply Chain Management\n• Proficiency in TMS\n• Proficiency in 3PL Management\n• Proficiency in Freight Forwarding\n• Proficiency in INCOTERMS\n• Proficiency in ERP Systems\n• Proficiency in Fleet Management\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Learning & development budget\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Gurgaon, Haryana, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with IRCTC Logistics!",
